    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
  </head>
  <body class="grain-overlay">
    <Header />
    <main>
      <article class="pt-32 pb-20">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
          <!-- Header -->
          <nav class="mb-8" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
            <ol class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-stone">
              <li><a href="/" class="hover:text-accent transition-colors">Home</a></li>
              <li><span class="mx-2">/</span></li>
              <li><a href="/blog" class="hover:text-accent transition-colors">Blog</a></li>
              <li><span class="mx-2">/</span></li>
              <li class="text-charcoal font-medium">AI Consulting Cost Guide</li>
            </ol>
          </nav>

          <div class="mb-8">
            <span class="text-sm text-accent font-medium uppercase tracking-wider">AI Consulting</span>
            <h1 class="heading-display text-4xl md:text-5xl mt-4 mb-4">
              How Much Does AI Consulting Cost? <em>A Complete Guide</em>
            </h1>
            <p class="text-stone">December 28, 2024 · 9 min read</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Content -->
          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
            <p class="text-xl text-stone leading-relaxed">
              "What's this going to cost?" It's the first question most business owners ask about AI consulting—and it's a fair one. Here's an honest breakdown of what AI consulting costs, what affects pricing, and how to think about ROI.
            </p>

            <h2 class="heading-display text-2xl mt-12 mb-4">The Short Answer</h2>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              AI consulting for small businesses typically ranges from <strong>$1,500 to $15,000</strong> for most projects. Enterprise-level implementations can run $50,000+, but those aren't what most small businesses need.
            </p>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Here's a rough breakdown:
            </p>

            <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-6 mb-6">
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center pb-4 border-b border-stone/20">
                  <span class="font-medium text-charcoal">AI Strategy Assessment</span>
                  <span class="text-accent font-display">$500 - $2,500</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center pb-4 border-b border-stone/20">
                  <span class="font-medium text-charcoal">Single Automation Implementation</span>
                  <span class="text-accent font-display">$1,500 - $5,000</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center pb-4 border-b border-stone/20">
                  <span class="font-medium text-charcoal">CRM + Automation Setup</span>
                  <span class="text-accent font-display">$3,000 - $10,000</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center pb-4 border-b border-stone/20">
                  <span class="font-medium text-charcoal">Comprehensive AI Implementation</span>
                  <span class="text-accent font-display">$8,000 - $25,000</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
                  <span class="font-medium text-charcoal">Ongoing Support (Monthly)</span>
                  <span class="text-accent font-display">$500 - $2,000/mo</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <h2 class="heading-display text-2xl mt-12 mb-4">What Affects AI Consulting Costs</h2>

            <h3 class="font-display text-xl mt-8 mb-3">1. Complexity of Implementation</h3>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              A simple lead follow-up automation costs less than a full <a href="/solutions/crm-automation/" class="text-accent hover:underline">CRM automation system</a> with multiple integrations. The more systems involved, the more configuration required, and the higher the cost.
            </p>

            <h3 class="font-display text-xl mt-8 mb-3">2. Customization Required</h3>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Off-the-shelf solutions with standard configurations cost less than custom-built automations. If your business has unique workflows or specific requirements, expect to pay more for tailored solutions.
            </p>

            <h3 class="font-display text-xl mt-8 mb-3">3. Number of Integrations</h3>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Connecting two systems is straightforward. Connecting five systems that all need to share data and trigger actions? That's more complex—and more expensive.
            </p>

            <h3 class="font-display text-xl mt-8 mb-3">4. Training Needs</h3>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Some businesses need extensive <a href="/services/ai-training/" class="text-accent hover:underline">team training</a> to use AI tools effectively. Others have tech-savvy teams that pick things up quickly. Training adds value but also adds cost.
            </p>

            <h3 class="font-display text-xl mt-8 mb-3">5. Consultant Experience and Location</h3>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Consultants in major metros often charge more than those in smaller markets. Experience level matters too—seasoned consultants charge more but often deliver faster, more reliable results.
            </p>

            <h2 class="heading-display text-2xl mt-12 mb-4">Pricing Models Explained</h2>

            <h3 class="font-display text-xl mt-8 mb-3">Project-Based Pricing</h3>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              A fixed price for a defined scope of work. You know exactly what you're paying before the project starts. This is most common for specific implementations like "set up automated lead follow-up" or "implement appointment scheduling."
            </p>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              <strong>Best for:</strong> Well-defined projects with clear deliverables.
            </p>

            <h3 class="font-display text-xl mt-8 mb-3">Hourly Consulting</h3>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Pay for actual time spent. Rates typically range from $100-$300/hour depending on expertise and location. Good for strategy sessions, training, or ongoing advisory work.
            </p>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              <strong>Best for:</strong> Advisory work, training sessions, or exploratory projects.
            </p>

            <h3 class="font-display text-xl mt-8 mb-3">Retainer/Monthly Support</h3>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Ongoing support for a fixed monthly fee. Includes monitoring, adjustments, troubleshooting, and strategy guidance. Typically $500-$2,000/month for small businesses.
            </p>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              <strong>Best for:</strong> Businesses that want ongoing optimization and support.
            </p>

            <h2 class="heading-display text-2xl mt-12 mb-4">How to Calculate ROI</h2>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              The real question isn't "what does it cost?" but "what's the return?" Here's how to think about AI ROI:
            </p>

            <h3 class="font-display text-xl mt-8 mb-3">Time Savings</h3>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              If you save 10 hours per week on manual tasks, and your time is worth $50/hour, that's $500/week or $26,000/year in recovered productivity. A $5,000 implementation pays for itself in about 10 weeks.
            </p>

            <h3 class="font-display text-xl mt-8 mb-3">Increased Conversions</h3>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              If faster lead response increases your close rate from 20% to 25%, and you get 100 leads per month worth $1,000 each, that's an extra $5,000/month in revenue.
            </p>

            <h3 class="font-display text-xl mt-8 mb-3">Reduced No-Shows</h3>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              If <a href="/solutions/appointment-automation/" class="text-accent hover:underline">automated reminders</a> reduce no-shows by 50%, and each no-show costs you $200 in lost revenue, the math adds up fast.
            </p>

            <div class="bg-charcoal text-cream rounded-2xl p-6 my-8">
              <h4 class="font-display text-lg mb-3">Quick ROI Calculator</h4>
              <p class="text-stone-light mb-4">Most well-implemented AI projects deliver 3-10x return on investment within the first year. If you're not seeing at least 2x ROI potential, it might not be the right project.</p>
            </div>

            <h2 class="heading-display text-2xl mt-12 mb-4">Red Flags in AI Consulting Pricing</h2>
            <p class="text-stone leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Watch out for these warning signs:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-stone mb-6">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-accent">•</span>
                <span><strong>No clear scope or deliverables.</strong> You should know exactly what you're getting.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-accent">•</span>
                <span><strong>Quotes that seem too good to be true.</strong> Quality work costs money. Rock-bottom prices often mean corners cut.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-accent">•</span>
                <span><strong>No mention of training or handoff.</strong> You need to understand and maintain what's built.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-accent">•</span>
                <span><strong>Pressure to decide immediately.</strong> Good consultants give you time to think.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-accent">•</span>
                <span><strong>No discovery process.</strong> If they quote without understanding your business, run.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="heading-display text-2xl mt-12 mb-4">Getting the Most Value from Your Investment</h2>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-stone mb-6">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Start with a strategy session.</strong> Identify highest-impact opportunities before diving into implementation.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Focus on quick wins first.</strong> Build momentum with projects that show fast ROI.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Invest in training.</strong> Your team's ability to use tools effectively determines long-term value.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" /></svg>
                <span><strong>Plan for ongoing optimization.</strong> AI systems improve with tuning. Budget for support.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>

            <div class="bg-cream rounded-2xl p-8 mt-12">
              <h3 class="font-display text-xl mb-4">Get a Custom Quote</h3>
              <p class="text-stone mb-4">
                Every business is different. The best way to understand what AI consulting will cost for your specific situation is to talk through your needs. Our consultations are free and no-obligation.
              </p>
              <a href="/#contact" class="btn-primary inline-flex">
                <span>Book Free Consultation</span>
              </a>
            </div>

            <!-- Related Posts -->
            <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-stone/20">
              <h3 class="font-display text-xl mb-6">Related Articles</h3>
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <a href="/blog/how-to-choose-ai-consultant/" class="group">
                  <div class="bg-cream rounded-xl p-4">
                    <span class="text-sm text-accent">AI Consulting</span>
                    <h4 class="font-display text-lg mt-1 group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">How to Choose the Right AI Consultant</h4>
                  </div>
                </a>
                <a href="/blog/ai-implementation-roi/" class="group">
                  <div class="bg-cream rounded-xl p-4">
                    <span class="text-sm text-accent">AI Consulting</span>
                    <h4 class="font-display text-lg mt-1 group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">AI Implementation ROI: What to Expect</h4>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
